The paper presents a deep learning model for the early prediction of sepsis in ICU patients. The model uses recurrent neural networks and survival analysis techniques to learn predictive features from clinical risk factors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
